COLOR. Carapace and legs reddish brown, with yellowish coxae, brownish sternum (
Fig. 29A–B
), abdomen dorsally dark gray and ventrally brownish.

PROSOMA. Carapace and ocular arrangement as shown in 
Fig. 29A
. Eye tubercle: 1.3 long; 1.4 wide. Distance AME-ALE 0.5. Eye diameters:AME 0.5,ALE 0.3, PME 0.2, PLE 0.4. Thoracic fovea procurved (
Fig. 27A
). Labium and sternum without cuspules (
Fig. 29B
). Basal segment of chelicerae with a prolateral row of 5 large teeth and 4–5 small retrolateral teeth in basal third (
Fig. 30A
), with proeminent rastellum, with 7–8 spines, with larger ones in distal region (
Fig. 30B
).

COLOR. Carapace and legs reddish brown, with yellowish coxae, brownish sternum (
Fig. 29J–K
), abdomen dorsally dark gray and ventrally brownish.

SPERMATHECAE. Base divided by non-sclerotized area. Ducts short and slightly narrower than receptacles, which are spherical and with evident granules (
Fig. 29L
).
